body:
I plugged in my moto g4 and the plugin discovered the device (yay!), but none of the run buttons are enabled:

![screen shot 2016-11-01 at 2 22 37 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5479/19908052/c28798ec-a03e-11e6-9726-31e299045e30.png)

I would expect that once a device is recognized, I'd be able to run on it.

Can we enable hot reload and run after I plug in a device?

comment_data.body: There's no launch configuration selected - to tell IntelliJ which app to run.

I've just had this problem as well.
- I 'Imported Folder' to load the Flutter/examples/flutter_gallery folder
- IJ asked me to 'enable the Flutter module' or some such. I accepted and it reopened the project.
- Ran Pub Get

I have the project displayed, and the iPhone simulator is correctly discovered, but no run button.

If restarting IntelliJ causes the buttons to be enabled then Luke's problem will be fixed with https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/pull/393

I'm not sure that will solve Seth's problem, though.

I have another branch ("enablement") I'm working on that will re-jigger buttons, so we'll need to loop back here once that's finished to see if the problem persists. That's still waiting on Flutter #6400 to be fixed (and we're working on that today).

> I wonder why?

I opened the gallery. Not sure if that matters.

> does this project have any run configurations?

Not sure how to tell?

> Not sure how to tell?

If you click the little chevron, are there any run configurations to choose from?

Nope:

![screen shot 2016-11-02 at 9 32 27 am](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5479/19937643/4c042e50-a0df-11e6-9e6e-f58280ee3b98.png)

I think @devoncarew suggested that we auto-populate that list for new projects (with Debug, Profile, and Release, to match the current `flutter run` modes).

FWIW I restarted IntelliJ and I still don't have Run Configs. So +1 for auto-populating them for newly imported/created projects.
@devoncarew : are there run configs in the gallery IML files?

Run configs are stored in .idea/worksapce.xml (if not shared) or in ./idea/runConfigurations/ folder (if shared). 

If Seth opened existing project there shouldn't be any run configs as New project wizard has not been invoked.

There is a run configuration committed in //examples/flutter_gallery. But more generally, I think the use case of newly created projects (`flutter create`) is covered; the flutter tool creates a launch config.
Can we create two default config when you import a new project?

There are no run configurations committed in /examples/flutter_gallery, and no .idea folder, i.e. no project. That means that if Seth opened /examples/flutter_gallery folder he effectively has CREATED a new project and it contains no run configurations.
But I see that there's .idea folder in the root of the flutter repo, i.e. there's an existing project configured, and this project has some run configurations committed.

Thanks Alex.

Sounds we have two things to do:
- When importing a Flutter project, auto-create common run configs
- Check-in the intellij project files for the Gallery
I believe this was fixed by https://github.com/flutter/flutter/commit/71900776afbf42eb184d855cad563e39e81c2ab7?
